## WooCommerce API Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values.
# The non-VITE vars are used by the dev proxy so secrets are NOT exposed to the browser.

# Secure server-side env (preferred)
WOOCOMMERCE_URL=https://your-woocommerce-site.com
WOOCOMMERCE_CONSUMER_KEY=your_consumer_key_here
WOOCOMMERCE_CONSUMER_SECRET=your_consumer_secret_here

# Legacy client-side env (not used by proxy, only here for backward compatibility; avoid in production)
VITE_WOOCOMMERCE_URL=https://your-woocommerce-site.com
VITE_WOOCOMMERCE_CONSUMER_KEY=your_consumer_key_here
VITE_WOOCOMMERCE_CONSUMER_SECRET=your_consumer_secret_here
# Tip: Op Vercel kun je deze óók instellen voor een directe client fallback
# (alleen als je proxy 403 geeft door host/firewall). Gebruik bij voorkeur READ-only keys.

# Instructions:
# 1. Go to WordPress Admin > WooCommerce > Settings > Advanced > REST API
# 2. Create a new API key (Read or Read/Write as needed). Prefer a READ-only key for the shop.
# 3. Fill WOOCOMMERCE_* values above (leave VITE_* empty in production builds).
# 4. Restart the dev server after changes to .env.